Data Types
Video Link: https://youtu.be/M_u1Obqe5Ns?si=DrErE7wP_Ji49z3H

1. Identifiers
Definition: These are names given to entities like classes, functions, or variables.

Naming Rules: Can consist of lowercase (a-z), uppercase (A-Z), digits (0-9), and underscores (_).

2. Keywords (Reserved Words)
Keywords are words that have a predefined meaning and functionality within Python.

3. Basic Data Types
String (str): A sequence of characters enclosed in double quotes.

Integer (int): Used for whole numbers.

Float: Used for decimal or floating-point numbers.

Boolean (bool): Represents one of two values: True or False.

4. Comments in Python
Purpose: Comments help developers understand the logic of the code during reviews.

Single-line Comments: Created using the # symbol.

Multi-line Comments: Created by enclosing text within triple double quotes (""").

Shortcut: In many editors, you can use Ctrl + / to toggle comments.
